This paper deals with the efficient computation of fastest paths in road networks, which involves graph algorithms and optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also introduces a heuristic function based on graph separators, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for solving optimization problems. The use of heuristics and optimization also suggests the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper deals with road networks, which can be modeled as graphs, and graph theory is a common topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). Finally, the paper presents experimental results, which suggests the category of machine learning (cs.LG) for evaluating the performance of the heuristic function.
